Large food retailers have told Parliament they prefer locally sourced poultry products to imports.Representatives of Woolworths Pick n Pay Shoprite Checkers Spar and Nando s were called by Parliament s trade and industry portfolio committee to account for their chicken-purchasing policies on Tuesday as part of the committee s hearings into the poultry industry crisis.The government poultry producers meat importers animal feed producers agricultural economists and others have also made submissions.Fast-food retailer Nando s said it used locally produced chicken only to support the local industry and to ensure the products were fresh. 